metadata.name: Décollage #398
metadata.description:
A generative sketch based on the concept of décollage, an artistic process that involves cutting or tearing pieces of an original image. The resulting outputs bear a resemblance to artworks produced using the lacerated poster technique, where posters are layered and torn to reveal parts of the posters underneath.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels. Note that this will not work with sizes beyond 5000 pixels.

(Allowlist is based on quantity of previous works owned).

metadata.name: Paradise Birds Generative Series #175
metadata.description: The Paradise Birds Generative Series is an abstracted representation of the flight of a bird and the aesthetic of the "paradise birds plant". The flight of the birds is randomly generated based on the hash provided. The system has 20 different color schemes, a varying number of birds and triangle sizes per artwork.

metadata.name: Nullteilung #41
metadata.description:
Nullteilung is another exercise in suprematism and composition. Born from a series of exercises in subdevision and tesselation, it seeks to connect with the user through the creation of a sense of order and balance in the composition.

The term "Nullteilung" a German word that can be translated to "zero division" which is suggesative of the order and disorder paramount in the piece, working toward a goal of emotional and programmatic purity.

metadata.name: Flexibility #10
metadata.description:
A circular composition made with the p5.js Perlin Noise. Polar coordinates are used in order to obtain the silk-like texture sometimes induced by the work.

From random numbers and trigonometry, this work has came to life and will help others to have a better life for themselves: 10% from primary + 10% from secondary will go to the Cure Parkinson's medical research.

Hope you admire this work as much as I do,

Carlz, 2023

metadata.name: Laniakea #71
metadata.description:
This piece captures the mysterious beauty of the Laniakea Supercluster, the colossal cosmic structure that contains our Milky Way galaxy.

A deep black backdrop is scattered with shimmering stars, evoking a sense of endless space and awe-inspiring expanse. Winds of dark matter are captured in the mid-ground, representing the invisible force that drives the formation of the galaxies within the Supercluster.

The foreground features a small spiral galaxy, shining brightly against the backdrop of the universe, reminding us that we are an integral part of an unimaginably grand structure.

metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #98
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.name: Another Side #17
metadata.description:
Emotions from within,
She looked on a new seas,
Light the secrets of summer hills,
Shaken into sleep by the cold,
Laid calm upon the transient skies till fate,
Twirled in the wave of an open hand,
Encircled by a delicate thin haze,
Black as the night on the other side.
_

Interactive feature :
* left or right clicks on visual screen to glitch it.

_

Generative visual, hybrid techniques, textures source created with AI (Stable Diffusion), combine with other elements that made with code / javascript, and layers transform in autonomous system on WebGL.
